# LearnPlay Development Rules

## 1. Browser Testing Policy (STRICT)

- **ALL browser testing MUST use webclaw** (`npx -y webclaw-mcp`)
- **ONLY webclaw is to take screenshots of browser pages** — never use any other screenshot tool or manual method
- **NEVER use Playwright** — Playwright is strictly forbidden in this project. Do not install, import, or reference Playwright anywhere
- **Remove all Playwright files and references** — If any Playwright code, scripts, or configuration exists, delete it immediately
- Use webclaw's `navigate_to`, `page_snapshot`, `click`, `type_text`, `screenshot`, and other browser tools for all visual verification
- When you need to verify UI changes, render correctness, or visual regression — use webclaw exclusively
- Use `evaluate` for JavaScript-based checks (reading DOM state, checking localStorage, etc.)
- Use `page_snapshot` to get an accessibility tree of the current page for interactive element identification

## 2. Technology Stack

### Frontend
- **React 18** — UI component library
- **TypeScript 5.6.3** — Static type checking
- **Vite 5.x** — Build tool and dev server
- **TailwindCSS 3.x** + `tailwindcss-animate` — Utility-first CSS framework
- **Radix UI** — Accessible, headless component primitives
- **wouter** — Lightweight routing
- **React Hook Form** + **Zod** + **zod-validation-error** — Form handling and validation
- **Framer Motion** — Animations
- **Recharts** — Data visualization / charts
- **@uppy/core**, **@uppy/dashboard**, **@uppy/aws-s3** — File uploads
- **socket.io-client** — Real-time client communication
- **@tanstack/react-query** — Server state management
- **embla-carousel-react**, **vaul**, **cmdk**, **input-otp**, **react-day-picker**, **react-resizable-panels** — Specialized UI components
- **lucide-react** — Icon library
- **react-icons** — Additional icon library
- **flag-icons** — Country flag icons
- **canvas-confetti** — Confetti animations
- **date-fns** + **date-fns-tz** — Date manipulation
- **clsx**, **tailwind-merge** — Conditional class name merging
- **class-variance-authority** — Component variant management
- **pptx-in-html-out**, **pptx-preview**, **docx**, **mammoth**, **pdf-parse**, **pdfkit**, **fast-xml-parser** — Document processing

### Backend
- **Express.js** — HTTP server framework
- **Socket.IO** — Real-time bidirectional communication
- **ws** — WebSocket implementation
- **Passport.js** + **passport-local** — Authentication
- **express-session** + **connect-pg-simple** — Session management with PostgreSQL store
- **bcrypt** — Password hashing
- **multer** — Multipart/form-data (file upload) parsing
- **nodemailer** + **mailersend** — Email sending
- **memoizee** — Function result caching
- **open-id-client** — OpenID Connect support
- **sharp** — Image processing
- **archiver**, **unzipper** — Archive handling
- **archiver** — Archive creation
- **axios** — HTTP client
- **wss** — WebSocket server
- **memoizee** — Caching

### Database
- **PostgreSQL** — Primary database
- **Drizzle ORM** (`drizzle-orm`) — Type-safe ORM
- **Drizzle Kit** (`drizzle-kit`) — Migration tooling
- **drizzle-zod** — Schema-to-Zod integration
- **@neondatabase/serverless** — Neon serverless PostgreSQL driver

### Testing
- **Jest** (`jest`) — Test runner and framework
- **ts-jest** — TypeScript support for Jest
- **Supertest** (`supertest`) — HTTP assertion library
- **@jest/globals** — Jest global functions
- **@types/jest** — TypeScript types for Jest

### Build Tools
- **Vite 5.x** — Frontend build tool and dev server
- **esbuild** — Server bundling (`@esbuild-plugins/node-globals-polyfill`, etc.)
- **TypeScript 5.6.3** — Static type checking
- **tsx** — Node.js runtime with TypeScript/ESM support
- **postcss** + **autoprefixer** — CSS processing
- **@vitejs/plugin-react** — React Fast Refresh plugin
- **tailwindcss** + **@tailwindcss/vite** + **@tailwindcss/typography** — TailwindCSS tooling

### Cloud/Storage
- **@google-cloud/storage** — Google Cloud Storage client
- **@replit/object-storage** — Replit object storage client
- **@google/genai** — Google Generative AI client

## 3. Project Structure

```
LearnPlayLocal/
├── Cloud-On-Prem/              # Main application codebase
│   ├── client/                  # Frontend (React + Vite)
│   │   ├── public/              # Static assets
│   │   └── src/                 # Source code
│   │       └── tests/           # Frontend tests
│   ├── server/                  # Backend (Express.js)
│   │   └── tests/               # Backend tests
│   ├── shared/                  # Shared code between client and server
│   ├── drizzle/                 # Drizzle ORM migrations
│   │   └── migrations/          # Migration files
│   ├── scripts/                 # Utility and validation scripts
│   ├── tests/                   # Integration/load tests (k6, etc.)
│   ├── cloud/                   # Cloud deployment scripts
│   ├── onprem/                  # On-prem deployment scripts
│   ├── contracts/               # Contract definitions
│   │   └── schema/              # Schema contracts
│   ├── vite.config.ts           # Vite configuration
│   ├── tailwind.config.ts       # TailwindCSS configuration
│   ├── drizzle.config.ts        # Drizzle ORM configuration
│   ├── tsconfig.json            # TypeScript configuration
│   └── package.json             # Dependencies
├── scripts/                     # Root-level utility scripts
├── memory-bank/                 # Project documentation (Memory Bank)
│   ├── projectbrief.md          # Project brief and goals
│   ├── productContext.md        # Product vision and context
│   ├── activeContext.md         # Current focus and recent changes
│   ├── systemPatterns.md        # Architecture and design patterns
│   ├── techContext.md           # Technology stack and setup
│   └── progress.md              # Status and known issues
└── .clinerules                  # This file
```

## 4. Deployment Modes

### Cloud
- Deployed to LearnPlay cloud infrastructure
- Base URL: `https://stcloud.learnplay.co.za` (staging)
- Configuration managed via `cloud/` scripts
- Deployment scripts: `cloud/master-install.sh`, `cloud/update.sh`

### On-Premise
- Self-hosted deployments
- Base URL: `https://stonprem.learnplay.co.za` (staging)
- Configuration managed via `onprem/` scripts
- Deployment scripts: `onprem/master-install.sh`, `onprem/update.sh`

Both modes share the same codebase but may have different configurations and deployment pathways.

## 5. Development Workflow

### Starting Development
```bash
cd Cloud-On-Prem
npm run dev              # Start dev server (tsx, single run)
npm run dev:watch        # Start dev server with file watcher
```

### Building
```bash
npm run build            # Full production build (Vite + esbuild)
```

### Validation & Auditing
```bash
npm run check            # Full validation suite (type checking, naming, governance, theme audits)
```

### Testing
```bash
npm run test                    # Full test suite
npm run test:server             # Backend tests only
npm run test:client             # Frontend tests only
npm run test:viewer-critical    # Critical path tests (viewer, navigation, translations, themes)
npm run test:critical           # All critical tests
npm run test:critical:integration  # Critical integration tests
npm run coverage                # Coverage report
```

### Database
```bash
npm run db:push                # Push schema to database (drizzle-kit push)
```

### Load Testing
```bash
npm run load:test:app2000:cloud       # 2000 user load test (cloud)
npm run load:test:app2000:onprem      # 2000 user load test (onprem)
npm run load:test:appshort:cloud      # Short profile load test (cloud)
npm run load:test:appshort:onprem     # Short profile load test (onprem)
```

### Migration Governance
```bash
npm run migration:validate                           # Validate migration governance
npm run migration:drift:check                        # Detect schema drift
npm run migration:verify:dev:cloud                   # Verify dev cloud migration
npm run migration:verify:dev:onprem                  # Verify dev onprem migration
npm run migration:verify:runtime:cloud               # Verify runtime contract (cloud)
npm run migration:verify:runtime:onprem              # Verify runtime contract (onprem)
```

## 6. Coding Standards

- **TypeScript strictly enforced** — All code should be fully typed
- **Zod for runtime validation** — Validate all external inputs at boundaries
- **Drizzle ORM for database operations** — Prefer Drizzle queries over raw SQL
- **Component composition** — Prefer small, composable components over monolithic ones
- **Server components and client components** — Clearly mark which is which
- **API responses should be Zod-validated** — Use schema validation for all API payloads
- **Follow existing naming conventions** — Snake case for DB columns/tables, camelCase in application code
- **Use environment variables** — Never hardcode secrets; use the secrets manager system

## 7. UI/Theming Guidelines

- **TailwindCSS** is the primary styling mechanism
- **Radix UI** provides accessible, headless component primitives
- **Theme system** supports dual-token architecture with branding themes
- **Accessibility**: Follow WCAG contrast ratios, use ARIA attributes, ensure keyboard navigation
- **Component contracts**: UI components have defined contracts validated by `check:theme-contracts`
- **Visual regression**: Theme rendering is audited via `check:theme-visual-regression`
- **UIKit parity**: Component consistency across cloud/onprem is checked via `check:uikit-parity`

## 8. API Development

- **RESTful endpoints** via Express.js
- **Real-time features** via Socket.IO
- **Session-based authentication** via Passport.js with `passport-local` strategy
- **All API responses should be Zod-validated** — Schema-first validation
- **Webhook events** are captured for deduplication and auditing
- **Database migrations** are managed via Drizzle in `drizzle/migrations/`
- **Migration naming**: Use descriptive SQL filenames with sequential numbering

## 9. Environment & Secrets Management

- **Never commit secrets** — Use the secrets manager scripts (`cloud/secrets-manager.sh`, `onprem/generate-vault.sh`)
- **Environment variables** are managed per deployment mode
- **Database credentials**, **API keys**, and **tokens** are stored in encrypted vaults
- **Sync admin parity**: Use `sync-admin-parity.sh` to maintain admin account consistency across environments

## 10. Data Processing & Document Handling

- **PDF processing**: `pdf-parse` for text extraction, `pdfkit` for generation
- **Document processing**: `mammoth` for .docx, `docx` for creation, `fast-xml-parser` for XML
- **Presentation handling**: `pptx-in-html-out` for parsing, `pptx-preview` for rendering
- **Image processing**: `sharp` for resizing, optimization, format conversion
- **Asset storage**: Google Cloud Storage or Replit Object Storage

## 11. AI/ML Integration

- **Google Generative AI** (`@google/genai`) for AI features
- **AI thumbnail generation**: Supported via migration `0009_ai_thumbnail_generation.sql`
- **AI columns on platform pricing**: Supported via migration `0060_add_platform_pricing_ai_columns.sql`

## 12. Enterprise Features

- **Enterprise portal**: Managed via migrations `0056-enterprise_portal.sql` through `0065-enterprise_demo_metrics_telemetry.sql`
- **License lifecycle**: Managed via migration `0062-enterprise_license_lifecycle_and_telemetry.sql`
- **Business profile fields**: Managed via migration `0063-enterprise_customer_business_profile_fields.sql`
- **Keyring system**: Managed via migrations `0057-enterprise_keyring.sql`, `0064-enterprise_metrics_and_royalty.sql`

## 13. Gamification & Content

- **Gamification catalog**: Defined in migration `0066_gamification_catalog_dedup_and_uniqueness.sql`
- **Course framework**: V2 segments in migration `0061_course_framework_v2_segments.sql`
- **Lesson/Topic structure**: Lessons scoped to topics via migration `0011_add_course_lessons_topic_id.sql`
- **Quiz system**: Generation enums in migration `0051_add_quiz_generation_enum.sql`, draft/source contracts in `0069_quiz_draft_source_contracts.sql`
- **Podcast system**: Pricing and ledger tables in `0070_podcast_pricing_no_loss_fields.sql` and `0071_podcast_ledger_tables.sql`

## 14. Translation & Internationalization

- **Translation index and analytics**: Migration `0072_translation_index_and_analytics.sql`
- **Platform theme singleton**: Migration `0073_platform_theme_singleton_index.sql`
- **Content translation active job uniqueness**: Migration `0100_content_translation_active_job_uniqueness.sql`

## 15. Communication Channels

When working on this project:
- Be concise and direct in code comments
- Follow existing patterns before introducing new ones
- Run `npm run check` before committing major changes
- Use webclaw for all browser-based verification
- Document any new migrations with clear SQL comments
- **MUST read ALL memory bank files at the start of every task**